SIMPLE: upwards
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Upwards
<hw>Up"wards</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>upweardes</ets>. See
<er>Up-</er>, and <er>-wards</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>In a direction from lower to higher; toward a higher
place; in a course toward the source or origin; -- opposed to
<xex>downward</xex>; <as>as, to tend or roll <ex>upward</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>I. Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Looking inward, we are stricken dumb; looking <qex>upward</qex>,
we speak and prevail.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In the upper parts; above.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dagon his name, sea monster, <qex>upward</qex> man,⟦br⟧
And down ward fish.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Yet more; indefinitely more; above; over.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From twenty years old and <qex>upward</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Num. i.
3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Upward of</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>Upwards
of</b></col></mcol>, <cd>more than; above.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have been your wife in this obedience⟦br⟧
<qex>Upward of</qex> twenty years.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Upward</ent>⟦br⟧
